cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper is primarily focused on routing in telecommunication networks, specifically in IoT networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses network topology design, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The addressing scheme proposed in the paper involves geographic coordinates and centrality measures, which could be related to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of routing, which could be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
